.TH cran2crux 1
.SH NAME
cran2crux \- Write CRUX ports for CRAN R modules
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B cran2crux
.SH DESCRIPTION

The \fIcran2crux\fP script automatically generates ready to use port(s) for
R-packages available from CRAN (\fhttps://cran.r-project.org/\fP) and BioConductor
(\fhttps://bioconductor.org/\fP). The script creates ports in the current
directory, which must be empty. The name of each port is "r4-foo" (lowercase) and
the release number is set to 1.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B "\-r, \-\-recursive"
Create port for an R-package and create ports for its dependencies and their own
dependencies, recursively.
.TP
.B "\-ro, \-\-recursive\-opt"
Create port for an R-package and create ports for its dependencies, as well as,
its optional dependencies, recursively. This may require to set <dependencies
depth> to a higher number (see below). This is rather slow and its usage
is discouraged.
.TP
.B "\-so, \-\-show\-old"
Check for potential updates of R-packages that are already installed. This
will report the versions as found at the upstream repository.
.TP
.B "\-u, \-\-update"
Generate updated ports for installed R-packages, that are reported to be outdated.
.TP
.B "\-h, \-\-help"
Display help.
.TP
.B "<dependencies depth>"
A positive integer after the \-r or \-ro option. This defines how many iterations of
recursive searches for dependencies cran2crux will perform. Set to a higher value
(>10) if dependencies list is expected to be large.

.SH CONFIG
You should configure \fI/etc/cran2crux.conf\fP to set a maintainer line, a CRAN
and Bioconductor mirrors, as well as the Bioconductor version. R syntax is used
(!), therefore settings go like this:

.PP
.nf
	maintainer.info <- c("Petar Petrov, slackalaxy at gmail dot com")
	cranrepo.url <- "https://cloud.r-project.org"
	bioc.url <- "https://bioconductor.org/packages/"
	bioc.version <- "3.23"

.SH EXAMPLES
.fi
.PP

Call \fIcran2crux\fP in a newly created, empty directory:
.PP
.nf
	mkdir rrr
	cd rrr 
	
This will create a port for an R-package:

	cran2crux Foo
	
This will create a port for Foo and dependencies recursively:

	cran2crux Foo -r
	
This will create a port for foo, its dependencies and optional
dependencies, recursively. This may require more intensive dependencies
searches, therefore we increase the depth value to 15:

	cran2crux Foo -ro 15

This will show potential updates of installed R-packages:

	cran2crux -so
	
This will generate updated ports for outdated R-packages already installed:
	
	cran2crux -u

.fi
.PP

.SH AUTHOR

\fIcran2crux\fP was written by Petar Petrov <slackalaxy@gmail.com> for CRUX.
